<br>
   Feeling refreshed, taking time to restock spells and heal, the group awakens. Everyone seems to be looking quite a bit better, with the exception of Maelgwyn. Maelgwyn looks healthier than ever, with the exception of her eyes. Her eyes now seem to be colored a dark gray where it once was white, and a brackish green where they used to be emerald.<br>
<br>
   Sapphire leads the group to the wooden door they had encountered previously and, with an adventurous shove, pushes it open. This opens to a grand courtyard, filled with exotic plants next to all the walls, surrounding a large cobbled center with three benches and a giant fountain in the center. To the right of the fountain are two grand wooden doors, which are in the center of a large stone wall, these doors seem to lead to outside of the monastery. The fountain, with a center stream of water that flies at least 15 feet high, seems to glisten in the sun. There seem to be seven large white stone rectangles portruding from around the fountain, replacing the cobbling. (ie. fountain is center, all of the floor is cobbled stone, with the exception of seven sections that butt up against the fountain.) Each rectangle is about nine feet long and four feet wide. <br>
      This area of the monastery (the courtyard), seems to have been untouched by the supposed battle. <br>
<br>
